'''Mount Avos''' was a [[Mountain/Legends|mountain]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]] which once housed a [[Spice/Legends|spice]] [[Mining/Legends|mine]]. It was part of the [[Hormick Range]] and was located near the [[Lycinder Plain]] and straddled the planet's equator. In [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]] Mount Avos was the site of the final battle of the [[Stark Hyperspace War/Legends|Stark Hyperspace War]], where a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] army under the command of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]] secured the conflict's final victory.

It was also the rendezvous point where [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]], [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]], [[Adi Gallia/Legends|Adi Gallia]], [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]], and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] were supposed to meet [[Ranulph Tarkin/Legends|Ranulph Tarkin]] and the rest of the survivors of the attack by [[Iaco Stark/Legends|Iaco Stark]]. Soon afterward they were met by [[Tholme/Legends|Tholme]] and [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]]. While moving further and further into the caverns of the mountain, Obi-Wan and Quinlan roused the [[challat eater]]s, insects native to the mountain, from their slumber. In an attempt to find an alternate way out of the mountain, the group of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] made their way to a nearby shipyard in search of a ship to get off the planet and deliver [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] Valorum back to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].

